Kevin Hassett, the newly sworn-in Chairman of the Council of Economic Advisers (CEA), expressed his gratitude to President Trump for the opportunity to serve the country. The CEA was established in 1946 to provide economic policy advice to the President. Hassett acknowledged the historical significance of the position, as he sat in the CEA conference room surrounded by portraits of former CEA Chairs. He also mentioned a note left by his predecessor, Jason Furman, emphasizing the enduring nature of the institution. Hassett expressed his excitement to begin his work as Chairman.